---

## Design decisions

| Area | Decision |
|---|---|
| **No real module required** | The `make_service` fixture contains an inline reference implementation so the test file is fully self-contained and runnable from the start. |
| **Parametrize for mandatory fields** | Every mandatory field is tested independently via `@pytest.mark.parametrize` so a failure points to exactly one field. |
| **Three-layer assertion** | For every error path the tests assert (1) the exception is raised, (2) nothing is persisted, and (3) no audit record is written. |
| **Audit content assertions** | Separate tests verify `action`, `entity_id`, `actor_id`, `before`, and `after` so a partial implementation is immediately visible. |
| **Edge cases** | Boundary ratings (1 & 5), equal date range, empty strings, special characters, and successive updates are covered. |
| **Fixture scope** | All fixtures are function-scoped (default) to guarantee test isolation. |

